  <exercise xml:id="ex-creating-a-branch">
    <introduction>
      <p>
        The <c>git branch [name]</c> command creates a new branch with the given <em>name</em>.  When creating a branch, you should give it a short but descriptive name (e.g. <em>FixTypoInReadme</em>).  Note: <em>name</em> may not have spaces, so you can use - (dashes) or CammelCaseText to divide words in your branch names.
      </p>

    </introduction>


    <task>
